    <h1><i>Computer Trivia Time!</i></h1>
    <p1><h2>Here are some fun trivia questions to test your knowledge of computers.</h2></p1>
    <p2>
        1. How many bits are in 1 byte?<br />
        a) 2<br />
        b) 4<br />
        c) 6<br />
        d) 8
    </p2><br /><br />
    <p3>
        2. Which of the following is NOT a function of the computer?<br />
        a) input<br />
        b) process<br />
        c) output<br />
        d) all of the above are functions of the computer
    </p3><br /><br />
    <p4>
        3. What does HTML stand for?<br />
        a)Hypertext Markup Language<br />
        b)Hypertext Makeup Language<br />
        c)Hypertext Mirror Language<br />
        d)Hypertext Monster Language
    </p4><br /><br />
    <p5>
        4. The decimal number 15 can be expressed as what number in binary?<br />
        a)1011<br />
        b)1111<br />
        c)1000<br />
        d)1101
    </p5><br /><br />
    <p6>
        5. Mark Zuckerberg founded what company in 2004?<br />
        a) Microsoft<br />
        b) Oracle<br />
        c) Facebook<br />
        d) Dropbox
    </p6><br /><br />
    <p7>ANSWERS:  1. d) 2. d) 3. a) 4. b) 5. c)</p7><br /><br />
